headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 34 points and 11 rebounds, and the Philadelphia 76ers beat the Charlotte Hornets 118-111 on Wednesday night for their fourth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid, 76ers continue dominance of Hornets, win 118-111

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 21 points, 14 rebounds and 10 assists despite sitting out the fourth quarter, and the Milwaukee Bucks routed the Indiana Pacers 130-110 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo gets triple-double as Bucks top Pacers 130-110

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 27 points and dished out 14 assists as the Dallas Mavericks snapped a six-game losing streak, defeating Trae Young and the Atlanta Hawks 122-116 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic, Mavericks snap 6-game skid, hold off Hawks 122-116

headlines.description: — Paul George made a season-high eight 3-pointers and scored 36 points, Kawhi Leonard added 24 and the Los Angeles Clippers found enough energy on tired legs to end a six-game road trip with a 121-99 victory over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Wednesday...
headlines.shortLinkText: George scores 36, Clippers use 3-pointers to drill Cavaliers

headlines.description: — Say this much for the Washington Wizards: They’re resilient.
headlines.shortLinkText: Beal scores 32, Wizards top reeling Heat 103-100

events.name: New York Knicks at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — Julius Randle scored 27 points and tied a career high by hitting five 3-pointers, and the New York Knicks beat the Chicago Bulls 107-103 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle scores 27 as Knicks hold off Bulls 107-103

events.name: Houston Rockets at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Kenrich Williams scored 19 points Wednesday night, and the Oklahoma City Thunder bounced back from a 30-point loss to Houston two days earlier and beat the Rockets 104-87.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williams scores 19; Thunder win rematch with Rockets 104-87

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 30 points and the San Antonio Spurs rallied from a 16-point deficit to beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 111-108 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs rally in final minutes to upend Timberwolves, 111-108

events.name: Phoenix Suns at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson punctuated a 28-point performance with a soaring, one-handed alley-oop jam during a decisive fourth-quarter surge, and the New Orleans Pelicans soundly defeated the Phoenix Suns 123-101 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williamson's 28 points lead Pelicans past Suns, 123-101

headlines.description: — De’Aaron Fox had 26 points and 11 assists, Buddy Hield made two free throws with six-tenths of a second remaining and the Sacramento Kings held off the short-handed Boston Celtics 116-111 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fox nets 26, Kings hold off short-handed Celtics 116-111
